comments: poetry hitting you on the face

"Well I fell in love

"Oh I did ma time, in the jail of your heart."
Excuse me, while i shapen my nails.
"...oh, the lies that you tell, i believe them so well.... take them back to your /red/ house..."
"Go on ahead and take this the wrong way."  You have to be really naive to think Dylan coined the term "sailor's mouth."
Given that the phrase "sailor's mouth" never appears in that song, I'd say it's probably not related.
I could see these lyrics being in an emo/indie song.  Hopefully Cobra Starship doesn't read this! *canned laughter*
Dylan's is cowboys mouth, sailor's mouth is a common expression, but Waits is probably fully aware of what Dylan wrote.

That "sailor's mouth" line is straight out of Bob Dylan's "Sad Eyed Lady of the Lowlands."  He's either paying it a tribute or stealing it.  Either way, I'm sure Tom was aware that the line was not his.
I fell in love with your sailor's mouth. damn
You cant always believe what Tom says in interviews, hes stated that he often makes things up which only adds to his mystique!

this is just too full of emotion. I hate people who shrug their shoulders at this song. I hate them. I hate them for being so void of feelings. I wish I could capture the song and enslave it in my head, but I guess others need it as well. Flow freely.
